EXTRACTED VALUE: Not that the game does anything bad, it is as unoriginal as you can get in this land of competition.
Combat is about as exciting as watching paint dry. [Aug 2001, p.112]
Hoverboards, combat, angsty riders, and a cabal-ruined New York City should at least make for an amusing game. Instead it's dreadfully boring.
I hated the movie, and I don't think any better of the game.
Sloppy emulation and a sloppier enhanced mode make this version of Tempest a package to avoid.
Dart board - £20, Darts - £5, Not having to play this game – Priceless.
